<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-NOTEBOOK-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BLOOM IS OFF THE ROSE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK BLAUDSCHUN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ It's tough to say who's more depressed this morning.
The people running the Rose Bowl or all those Nebraska backers who
already had made their holiday travel plans to Phoenix so they
could watch their beloved Huskers compete for the national
championship in the Fiesta Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   The reason for Nebraska's depresssion is obvious. Check out
Saturday's result: No. 18 Texas A&AMP;M 28, No. 2 Nebraska 21. Bye-bye
Phoenix, so long and farewell to a chance to win another national
title. At least not in the Fiesta Bowl. And not without lots of
help from lots of other teams who are ahead of them, including Big
12 rival Kansas State.
</P>
<P>
   The Huskers saw their 19-game winning streak end. ``We're down
and hurt right now,'' said first-year coach Frank Solich, who
watched his team barely survive upstart Oklahoma State a week ago.
``We're not accustomed to taking a loss.''
</P>
<P>
   Nor is Texas A&AMP;M accustomed to handing them out, at least not to
Top 5 teams. The win over Nebraska was the Aggies' first against a
Top 5 team since 1975.
</P>
<P>
   As for the Rose Bowl's woes? How would you like to be on the
Rose Bowl committee this morning? For decades, the esteemed
gentlemen in the white suits pined for a Big Ten/Pac-10 matchup of
No. 1 vs. No. 2 for the national championship.
</P>
<P>
   It never happened. Now it could, with Ohio State No. 1 and UCLA
No. 2 in Sunday's polls. Only problem is, if things stay that way,
the dream matchup will be played in the Fiesta Bowl, which will
host this season's national championship game.
</P>
<P>
   The only escape hatch for the Rose Bowl could be the continued
improvement of Notre Dame, which rolled over Arizona State Saturday
night and has a clear shot at earning a Bowl Championship Series
at-large slot. If that happens, and the Rose Bowl loses either the
Pac-10 champion or Big Ten champion to the Fiesta, count on the
Irish being in Pasadena on New Year's Day.
</P>
<P>
   The other Nervous Nellie out there is Kansas State, which is now
top dog in the Big 12 after its victory over Colorado and
Nebraska's defeat. The Wildcats still have that monster grudge
match with the Huskers in November, but right now they are the team
with the clearest path to the Big 12 championship game in St. Louis
and a BCS slot, perhaps in the Fiesta.
</P>
<P>
   All of this may be a bit premature, of course, but Showdown
Saturday, as some are calling it, cleared some of the murkiness
from the national championship picture.
</P>
<P>
   Right now, the best bets for the Fiesta Bowl matchup are either
Ohio State vs. Tennessee or Ohio State vs. UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA will know more when it faces unbeaten Oregon at the Rose
Bowl Saturday. With so much at stake, one wonders if Bruins
officials will decide to reschedule that canceled game against
Miami.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There is no clear-cut favorite in the Heisman Trophy race now,
although Texas's  &UR; Ricky Williams &LR; , &UR;  &LR; who picked up 139 yards and
scored two touchdowns in the Longhorns' 34-3 win over Oklahoma, and
UCLA quarterback  &UR; Cade McNown &LR; , &UR;  &LR; who threw a pair of touchdown
passes in the Bruins' 52-28 romp over Arizona, seem to be slightly
ahead of the pack ... Nebraska also lost a 40-game regular-season
winning streak ... Poor Auburn. The Tigers, who according to the
NCAA computer have the toughest schedule in college football, can't
catch a break. Their 38-21 loss to Mississippi State Saturday
dropped them to 1-4, their worst start in 46 years ... Is North
Carolina's defense back? The Tar Heels, who struggled through the
early part of the season, held Pittsburgh to 181 yards in total
offense and only 48 yards rushing in a 29-10 win. Or maybe Pitt
isn't that good ... Say hello to the new Prairie View. Cheney
State's 50th straight game without a victory, a 42-22 loss to
Kutztown, set a Division 2 record. Cheney also has the longest
current losing streak, 37 games ... Talk about a bad day. St.
Mary's (Calif.) lost, 49-0, to Utah and lost six fumbles, threw
four interceptions, and rushed for minus-29 yards ... Washington
had 13 sacks in a 53-12 win over Utah State ... With Nebraska's
loss, UCLA's 14-game winning streak is the longest in Division 1-A
... How sore is Purdue quarterback  &UR; Drew Brees  &LR; this morning? Brees
completed an NCAA record 55 passes (in 83 attempts) in a 31-24 loss
to Wisconsin. ``My arm is fine,'' Brees said. ``I can't believe we
lost the game.'' ... Arkansas and Oregon are a combined 11-0.
Neither was ranked in the preseason ... California scored 22 points
in a five-minute stretch in turning a 31-10 deficit to USC into a
32-31 victory ... Don't look now, but Virginia and Georgia Tech are
leading the ACC ... South Carolina is 1-5 after losing to Kentucky
Saturday, which puts Gamecocks coach  &UR; Brad Scott  &LR; on the endangered
species list.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-12-98 0135EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
