<HEADLINE>
BRIERE CLOSE TO RETURNING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN AND TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Daniel Briere won't rush it, but the Coyotes center hinted that
he could play with the team next Monday when the Boston Bruins come
to town.
</P>
<P>
   ``I won't be ready Thursday, that's for sure, but after that,
who knows? I think I might be ready,'' said Briere, sidelined
because of a concussion after getting dumped by Anaheim's  &UR; Ruslan
Salei in the final preseason game. ``I rode the bike (Sunday), got
in a little workout, and I was feeling pretty good, actually. There
were no symptoms.''
</P>
<P>
   Briere, who led the team in scoring during the preseason with
seven points, will skate alone today and Tuesday and possibly will
resume regular practices with the team within a few days.
</P>
<P>
   As for the five-game suspension and $1,000 fine that was handed
down to Salei, Briere said the punishment fit the crime. Sort of.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's hard to say. It's your life you're talking about there,
and I was in and out (of consciousness) for a few minutes,'' he
said. ``Maybe it should have been for more games, but at the same
time, I think the league's going to be better about stuff like that
this year. They're going to take more action against those kinds of
cheap shots.''
</P>
<P>
   After spending five straight full seasons in the minor leagues
and missing virtually all of training camp with the Coyotes because
of sprained knee ligaments, defenseman
 &UR; Bryan Helmer finally appeared in his first NHL game Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was a little nervous at the start, but after a while, I felt
pretty good,'' said Helmer, 26, who signed as a free agent this
summer after getting caught in a logjam with the New Jersey Devils,
who are talent-rich in blue liners. ``I just wish it would have
went the other way with a win. But it was finally nice to get my
chance.''
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman  &UR; Deron Quint was scratched from the opener, the
result of a concussion he received late in the final preseason game
against Anaheim.
</P>
<P>
   ``It should be only another four or five days,'' said Quint, who
also has a cut on his chin and upper lip after receiving a high
stick on the play. ``I hope to be back in time for Thursday night's
game against Colorado.''
</P>
<P>
   Wing  &UR; Brad Isbister was a healthy scratch. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
