<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN13-COX_President Clinton may yet pull an
education-policy rabbit out of the empty-hat 105th Congress, but
either way, the 105th will soon and mercifully relieve us of
itself, to go home and seek license from the voters to act out
again next year. It is a dismal prospect, which voters, if the
current soundings prove right, will ratify in perhaps historically
small numbers.
</P>
<P>
   (TEEPEN, Cox News Service)
