<P>
   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   VIAGRA-MILITARY (San Antonio) _ Active-duty and retired military
people in San Antonio soon will have access to Viagra, the little
blue pill that's helped thousands of men overcome impotence.
Exactly when that will happen is unknown. By SIG CHRISTENSON.
</P>
<P>
   INFERTILITY (San Francisco) _ For all the advances in fertility
treatments, one grim fact remains: Women's eggs begin a sharp
decline in viability after age 35, and by age 45 few can conceive
their own biological children. Emerging techniques could provide
better answers to the problem of aging eggs. By ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
<P>
   INFIDELITY (San Francisco) _ Infidelity and sex. Always
tantalizing subjects, they have gone beyond the bedroom, tabloids
and talk shows to the national news arena, thanks to the
never-ending saga of Bill Clinton and Monica Lewinsky. Just what is
infidelity? And can those marriages be saved? By MARIANNE
COSTANTINOU.
</P>
<P>
   STUDY-TUNES (Troy, N.Y.) _ Hudson Valley Community College has
established a Mozart Effect Study Area, believing that the soothing
sounds of classical music help students tune into their homework.
Students and faculty members say it works. By MICHELE MORGAN
BOLTON.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FLOOD-TRAUMA (Del Rio, Texas) _ Victims of the flooding that
ravaged a poor section of this Texas border city in August have
used faith to try to rebuild their shattered lives. But ministers
and relief workers acknowledge that the death and damage have
shaken even the most faithful. By JOHN GUTIERREZ-MIER
</P>
