<P>
   KENNEWICK-MAN (Undated) Kennewick Man is a scientific celebrity,
a cause celebre. The 9,300-year-old skeleton has been dubbed ``the
most significant archaeological find of the decade.'' Prominent
scientists are suing the federal government seeking access to study
him, arguing his bones are ``of major significance for science and
American prehistory.'' Native Americans claim the bones are those
of an ancestor, contending the ``Ancient One'' should be reburied
and is not the property of scientists. The federal lawsuit, which
has pitted scientists against the tribes, will resolve the question
of who gets first dibs on the bones. If Kennewick Man is determined
to be Native American, the tribes' claim may prevail. But the bones
are so ancient that determining ancestry is no simple matter.
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
