   NETWATCH-COX_In the precarious world of online magazines,
necessity is clearly the mother of invention. Just as the smoke
cleared from Salon magazine's Washington fiasco, which culminated
in the resignation of D.C. bureau chief Jonathan Broder and a whole
lot of publicity, Salon was back in the news with a new business
model. For $25 a year, readers can now become members. (KATZ,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
