<P>
   JAPAN-ECON (Tokyo) _ Japan's Parliament approves long-awaited
legislation allowing the government to take over or shut down
troubled banks, amid signs that political parties may be near
agreement on a broad package for reviving the banking system that
could cost more than $400 billion. By Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
