<SLUG> BC-ADULTERY-INSURANCE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
$2 BUYS INFIDELITY INSURANCE 
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
By JENIFER HANRAHAN 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Worried about your spouse cheating? Now you can
cover yourself _ with an ``insurance policy'' to protect your
dignity in case of unfaithfulness.
</P>
<P>
   Infidelity Life now offers coverage against ``intentional,
unintentional and/or passive infidelities.'' The $2 policy is good
for the term of the marriage, no less.
</P>
<P>
   What is passive infidelity, you ask? ``Lusting in your heart and
premeditated flirting,'' said Bill Singletary, company president.
</P>
<P>
   The coverage, of course, isn't an insurance policy in the
strictest sense of the word. Infidelity Life is a subsidiary of TMR
Multimedia, a novelty marketing company based in Hallandale, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Upon submission of proof of a spouse's infidelity, the insured
will receive the following: A really nasty letter addressed to the
cheating party, peppered throughout with lots of name-calling and
righteous indignation; a list of good divorce lawyers; a fake but
still inspirational ``keep-your-chin-up'' note from Hillary
Clinton; a scarlet letter ``A'' applique; and bipartisan
corroboration by 10 registered Democrats and Republicans, said
Singletary.
</P>
<P>
   If you are the cheater _ either accused or caught outright _
you'll receive your own personal press release containing 25
categorical denials of wrongdoing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was not unfaithful with !ital!that!off! person,'' for
instance.
</P>
<P>
   You'll get five hair-splitting definitions of the term
infidelity that would make Clinton proud and a ``blanket apology
and atonement proviso for any unintentional harm caused to family
and/or friends.''
</P>
<P>
   When you get tired of groveling and are ready to strike back,
you'll also receive a list of your accuser's vices addressed to
his/her employer, clergyman, friends and mother.
</P>
<P>
   Singletary said he was inspired by none other than the Clintons.
</P>
<P>
   ``This country is at a new low for perverseness,'' he said.
``Turn on CNN, and you see infidelity. My God, it's coming out of
the woodwork. Something's gone wrong. Everybody seems to be
sleeping with everyone else other than their spouse.''
</P>
<P>
   Might as well cash in. &UR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
