<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-12 19:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2619 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ENTERTAINMENT-BUDGET-     10-12 0200
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-BUDGET-RESEND-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Bob McCarthy
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
. 
ADULTERY-WHY (Los Angeles) _ Why has America been so willing to
forgive President Clinton for his ``inappropriate relations'' with
Monica Lewinsky? Could it be because a hefty percentage of
Americans have themselves experienced adultery? Could it be that
Clinton's videotape testimony was actually a window into many
American bedrooms? We talk to cheated spouses, psychotherapists,
social scientists about the consequences of flirting with disaster
_ and why we still do it. By Jenifer Hanrahan. 
. 
ADULTERY-INSURANCE (Los Angeles) _ Infidelity Life now offers
coverage against infidelity for $2. Coverage, however, isn't an
insurance policy in the strictest sense of the word. The injured
party receives a nasty letter addressed to the cheating party, a
list of good divorce lawyers, and a ``keep-your-chin-up'' note from
Hillary Clinton. By Jenifer Hanrahan. 

